Personal Finance Dashboard
Description

This Personal Finance Dashboard is a Python-based tool that allows users to visualize and categorize their personal financial transactions. Utilizing libraries like pandas, numpy, tkinter, and panel, the dashboard offers a comprehensive view of expenses, incomes, savings, and more.
Features

    File Browsing: Select financial data files for analysis.
    Data Cleaning and Processing: Clean and process transaction data for accurate categorization.
    Dynamic Categorization: Automatically categorize transactions into predefined categories like Groceries, Rent, Eating Out, etc.
    Monthly Summary: Generate summaries of the latest month's income, recurring and non-recurring expenses, and savings.
    Interactive Dashboard: View your financial data through interactive charts and tables.

Installation

To use this dashboard, you need to have Python installed on your computer. Additionally, the following Python libraries are required:

bash

pip install pandas numpy panel hvplot holoviews

Usage

    Start the Program: Run the script to open the file dialog and select your CSV file containing the transaction data.
    Data Processing: The script will automatically process and categorize your transactions.
    View Dashboard: The dashboard will be displayed with various widgets and visualizations.

File Format

Your financial data should be in a CSV format with the following columns:

    Date
    Description
    Amount
    Transaction Type
    Account Name

